name: Date Lines Yellow 6x6 B mixed media art
description:
Date Lines Yellow 6x6 A mixed media art piece, comprised of wood with wire and various mediums. Hangs via one keyhole hanger, flush with wall.

Date Lines is a mixed media exploration of Star St.Germain's failed
adventures in the San Francisco dating scene. Star's various suitors are represented as silhouettes, faceless
testaments to all manner of sexy mistakes. The collection is about finding hope amongst the most dismal of interactions--with hilarious results.

name: No More Nightmares digital painting
description:
12x14 inch digital painting, printed on canvas with a gloss finish and finished as a ready-to-hang gallery wrap. Comes with the new Dead When I Found Her CD, Rag Doll Blues.

Coinciding with the release of the sophomore album "Rag Doll Blues" by Portland electronic-industrial band Dead When I Found Her, this series is an experiment in deconstructing a final work into its constituent pieces and rearranging them into a thematically-intertwined narrative structure. The images are derived from the "Rag Doll Blues" album art, conceived and executed by band member John C. Worsley, constrained within sequential panels, and lettered with an ad-hoc narrative consisting of Michael Arthur Holloway's lyrical snippets from the album. The result is a story more like a fever dream than a traditional comic-book.
